<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,1519,1618]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1519,1545]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Comments.</emphasis>
Synonymy and Diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[637,771,1520,1545]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Hippasteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[637,771,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Hippasteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extensive. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mah, C. L. &amp; Neill, K &amp; Eleaume, M. &amp; Foltz, D." box="[934,1132,1519,1545]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="422 - 456" refId="ref48107" refString="Mah, C. L., Neill, K, Eleaume, M. &amp; Foltz, D. (2014) New Species and global revision of Hippasteria (Hippasterinae: Goniasteridae; Asteroidea; Echinodermata). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 171, 422 - 456. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12131" type="journal article" year="2014">
Mah 
<emphasis box="[996,1055,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2014
</bibRefCitation>
a) identified seven species within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[229,363,1556,1581]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Hippasteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,363,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Hippasteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using the 
<emphasis box="[475,711,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">cytochrome oxidase I</emphasis>
gene subunit, with some lineages displaying a complex or cluster of multiple species. The relevant subdivision is referred to herein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
